21:Tf3b,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does AI call handling cost for locksmiths?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Whoza.ai starts at £59/month for the Starter plan. One captured emergency lockout averages £80-£150 callout fee. A full security upgrade can be £500-£2,000. At £59/month, one emergency lockout callout pays for the entire year. Overage minutes are billed at £0.26/minute. No hidden fees or contracts."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can Katie handle emergency lockout calls at 3am?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Katie answers 24/7, 365 days a year. She identifies lockout emergencies by keywords like 'locked out', 'lost keys', 'broken key', 'snapped key', 'can't get in', 'urgent', and 'emergency' — and marks the enquiry as emergency priority. You get an immediate WhatsApp with 'LOCKOUT EMERGENCY — URGENT' in the header, even at 3am on Christmas Day."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What information does Katie collect from lockout customers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Katie collects: full name, phone number, postcode, property type (house/flat/commercial), lock type (if known — Yale, Chubb, euro cylinder, mortice, digital), how they got locked out (lost keys, broken key, snapped in lock, locked inside, lock failure), whether it's a tenant or landlord situation, number of locks affected, and how they found you."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can Katie distinguish between a residential lockout and a commercial security job?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Katie is trained to identify the type of locksmith job from the customer's description. 'Locked out of my house' gets residential lockout priority. 'Need to change all locks on my rental property' gets landlord/multi-property tagging. 'Security survey for my shop' gets commercial security priority. Each type gets different follow-up handling in your dashboard."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does Katie handle UPVC door lock and window lock enquiries?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Katie recognises UPVC-specific terminology like 'euro cylinder', 'multipoint lock', 'mechanism failure', 'window lock', 'patio door', and 'French door'. She captures the specific issue and marks it as 'UPVC specialist' in your dashboard so you know to bring the right replacement parts."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does whoza.ai help with key cutting and key replacement enquiries?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Katie captures key replacement enquiries with: type of key (house key, car key, safe key, padlock key), whether it's a standard key or high-security key, number of copies needed, and whether the customer can bring the lock or key to you. She can also ask if they need the lock rekeyed or just a key cut."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can Katie handle calls about security upgrades and CCTV?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Katie identifies security upgrade calls by keywords like 'security survey', 'CCTV', 'alarm', 'smart lock', 'digital lock', 'keyless entry', and 'high security'. She captures: property type, number of entry points, current security level, budget range, and preferred survey date. These high-value enquiries (£500-£3,000+) get flagged as 'security upgrade' for priority follow-up."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Will customers trust an AI with their lockout emergency?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Katie introduces herself as your AI assistant and explains that she's capturing details so you can respond immediately. Most lockout customers are relieved to speak to someone right away rather than leaving a voicemail. Katie reassures them that their locksmith has been notified and will call back within minutes. In our surveys, 89% of callers are satisfied with the AI experience."}}]}15:["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$21"}}]
